content:
The `DashboardLayout` component serves as the main layout for the dashboard section of the application. It wraps the dashboard content with a `ToastProvider` for managing toast notifications and arranges a `Sidebar` alongside the main content area.

**Key Exports/Functions:**

*   `DashboardLayout`: A React component that defines the structure of the dashboard. It accepts `children` as a prop, which represents the content to be displayed within the layout.

**Props:**

*   `children`: `React.ReactNode` - The content that will be rendered within the main area of the dashboard.

**Usage Example:**

```typescript
// app/dashboard/page.tsx
import DashboardLayout from './layout';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <DashboardLayout>
      {/* Dashboard specific content goes here */}
      <h1>Welcome to your Dashboard!</h1>
    </DashboardLayout>
  );
}
```

